summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of $525 from the general fund of the City of Seattle, to pay claim of Edward Braithwaite and Margaret Braithwaite, his wife, for personal injuries received by Margaret Braithwaite on the 11th day of April 1916, between the hours of 4:30 o' clock and 5 o' clock p.m., while traveling southward upon the east sidewalk of 12th Avenue Northeast, at a point about 222 feet from the intersection of said 12th Avenue Northeast and East 38th Street, approximately in front of a dwelling, No. 3817 12th Avenue Northeast, in the City of Seattle and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
